Description. FEMALE. Length of idiosoma 605 , width 405 . Idiosomal dorsum (
Fig. 1
). Central plate with 2 pairs of setae c 1 and d 1 ; intercalary plates paired. All plates coarsely reticulated; Postocular bodies very large, with weak reticulate pattern (
Fig. 26
). Eyes absent. Striation anterolateral to propodosomal plate with microtubercles (
Fig. 27
). Setae ve , sce , c 2 , d 2 , and e 2 conspicuously longer than others, smooth and pointed. Other dorsal setae distinctly blunt-ended and barbed in distal half. Ratio ve/sci = 2.5. Length of dorsal setae:
